## 🐛 Bug Report

Stream writing a large workbook produces a corrupted file. Attempting to read the file with Excel results in "Repair required". Attempting to read with ExcelJS results in "Error: invalid signature: 0x...."

Lib version: 4.4.0, 4.4.1-prerelease.0, and every version down to 4.0.1 at least

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
import ExcelJS from "exceljs";

const file = "file.xlsx";
const rowCount = 10_000_000;

const writer = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter({ filename: file });
const writeWorksheet = writer.addWorksheet(defaultWorkbookWorksheetName);

const cells = ["x".repeat(400)];
for (let r = 0; r < rowCount; r++) {
	const row = writeWorksheet.addRow(cells);
	row.commit();
}

writeWorksheet.commit();
await writer.commit();

const reader = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookReader(file, {});
for await (const readWorksheet of reader) { // <== Error: invalid signature: 0xc3bcae2b
	console.log("This never occurs");
}
```

Interestingly the "Invalid signature" value changes depending on the written data.

## The expected behaviour:

A properly formatted XLS file to be produced and readable.
